Description: Add Lokker app (https://github.com/tim-ecoder/Lokker.git) as privileged system app.
Version: v1.2a

Files:
  device/blackberry/athena/prebuilt/Lokker.apk  — prebuilt APK from GitHub releases
  device/blackberry/athena/prebuilt/Android.bp   — prebuilt module definition
  device/blackberry/athena/prebuilt/com.lokker.app.privapp-permissions.xml — privileged permissions
  device/blackberry/athena/device.mk             — added Lokker to PRODUCT_PACKAGES

Install location: system_ext/priv-app/Lokker/Lokker.apk
Signed with: platform certificate (re-signed by build via certificate: "platform")
APK source: https://github.com/tim-ecoder/Lokker/releases/tag/Lokker-v1.2a
Privileged permissions: MANAGE_USERS, CHANGE_COMPONENT_ENABLED_STATE, REMOVE_TASKS,
  REAL_GET_TASKS, WRITE_SECURE_SETTINGS, MANAGE_ACTIVITY_STACKS

LOS23 note: Unlike LOS22, no dex preprocessing is required. The Android.bp module uses
`certificate: "platform"` so Soong re-signs the APK during the build, which also
decompresses/recompresses the package under the platform key. Drop the upstream
GitHub-release APK into prebuilt/ and the build takes care of the rest.

Module definition (device/blackberry/athena/prebuilt/Android.bp):

  android_app_import {
      name: "Lokker",
      apk: "Lokker.apk",
      certificate: "platform",
      privileged: true,
      system_ext_specific: true,
      dex_preopt: {
          enabled: false,
      },
      required: [
          "com.lokker.app.privapp-permissions",
      ],
  }

  prebuilt_etc {
      name: "com.lokker.app.privapp-permissions",
      system_ext_specific: true,
      sub_dir: "permissions",
      src: "com.lokker.app.privapp-permissions.xml",
      filename_from_src: true,
  }
